ser</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/14/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4:19:18 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/adsogda/images/arlos.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: This Weekends crap 4/14-4/16</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Glub, in the cases where I observed this, the zone was actually starting to be pretty emtpy. There weren't roaming anything in the area. Indeed, I was never pulling any closer to the camp spot than, say, pulling from generally near the SW corner when people were camped at the NW corner. I also made quite sure to pull close to the zone wall (without running up it) so as to be as far out from aggro radius of anything to the east as possible.<br>
<br>
I saw a case where the enchanter died after a pull of a single mob. No one else who was on had any aggro to cazic, not even the puller. We braved the amy onslaught and waited for the DT minute to pass. No one else got hit. <br>
<br>
Now, I am, as I said, entirely willing to believe cazic was getting aggro from SOMEWHERE, but however it's happening, it's fubar'ed. And it never was anyone in the pull group that got hit either, which makes it even more screwy. The only thing the enchanter would ever cast at me is the very occasional augment too, so it wasn't a case of someone healing/buffing the puller getting toasted either.<br>
<br>
Ultimately, I didn't make my post to try and argue with you. I posted to be nice and let you guys know, &quot;Hey, this seemed different, and is something that you might want to look out for.&quot; You know, helping each other out, passing along info, etc. Sorry it somehow turned into an argument (and something of a flame by you implying I don't know what I'm doing.) Yes, I'm newish in the planes. No, I wasn't the only one finding it strange and different how it was behaving, everyone there was. So, anyway, what I posted was my observation, if you want to doubt or disagree with it, tis of course your perogative.<br>
<br>
